FT  29 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Adwest
Adwest Group, the automotive components, defence and property company, has
acquired Modular Devices from private owners. The consideration in cash
involves a maximum initial payment of Dollars 11m (Pounds 7.5m) for net
assets of Dollars 3.44m plus a maximum profit-related Dollars 2.5m.
Modular Devices is a California-based designer and maker of commercial power
supply units for specialist computer equipment manufacturers. It made
pre-tax profits of Dollars 1.1m on sales of Dollars 12.9m in the year to
June 30 1993.
